If no kin was defined, this method will function as a shortcut for [`Message::get()`][link:get].

~~~ .php.xmp
Message::{$any}($text, $vars = [], $preserve_case = false);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
Message::error('create');
Message::info('create');
Message::success('create');
Message::warn('create');

Message::foo('create');
Message::bar('create');
~~~

> **Note:** Calling `Message::error()` and `Message::warn()` will increase the internal `Message::$x` value. This is useful for checking errors before doing something:
>
> ~~~ .php
> if (!Message::$x) {
>     File::set('test')->saveTo('success.log');
> }
> ~~~